<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911003-0049</DOCNO><DOCID>911003-0049.</DOCID><HL>   Computer Associates   Says U.S. Seeks Data   On Pansophic Tender</HL><DATE>10/03/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B2</SO><CO>   CA PNS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>SOFTWARE (SOF)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><GV>JUSTICE DEPARTMENT (JUS)</GV><RE>ILLINOIS (IL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   GARDEN CITY, N.Y. -- Computer Associates InternationalInc. said the Justice Department asked for additionalinformation on the company's pending acquisition of PansophicSystems Inc.   A Computer Associates spokeswoman said the request was&quot;not unusual.&quot; Computer Associates entered into a definitiveagreement last month to buy Pansophic for $290 million, or$16.15 a share, through a tender offer. The offer, originallyscheduled to expire Oct. 10, will be extended indefinitely,Computer Associates said. Pansophic, based in Lisle, Ill.,would be merged with one of Computer Associates'subsidiaries.</LP><TEXT>   Both Pansophic and Computer Associates make software,primarily for mainframe and midsized computer systems.Pansophic, which had net income of $20.6 million on revenueof $230.2 million in the fiscal year ended April 30,specializes in programs for data-base management, logisticsmanagement and computer-aided software engineering.   Computer Associates, which earned $159.3 million onrevenue of $1.35 billion in the fiscal year ended March 31,focuses on utility, data-base and applications software.   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,Pansophic closed at $15.625, down 25 cents, and ComputerAssociates closed at $7.625, down 25 cents.</TEXT></DOC>